thread.title: Royals beat Astros 7-2, will now face Blue Jays in ALCS
thread.title_full: Royals beat Astros 7-2, will now face Blue Jays in ALCS

author: Dave Skretta
title: Royals beat Astros 7-2, will now face Blue Jays in ALCS
text:
Johnny Cueto was dominant in Game 5 of the American League Division Series against the Houston Astros on Oct. 14, 2015, in Kansas City, Mo. (Orlin Wagner/AP) Royals beat Astros 7-2, will now face Blue Jays in ALCS By Dave Skretta KANSAS CITY, Mo — The Associated Press 
Published Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 11:21PM EDT 
Last updated Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 11:27PM EDT 
Johnny Cueto delivered a masterpiece on his biggest stage yet, pitching eight dominant innings Wednesday night and leading the never-say-die Kansas City Royals to a 7-2 victory over the Houston Astros and back to the American League Championship Series. 
Cueto allowed two hits, a single by Evan Gattis followed by Luis Valbuena’s second-inning homer, before retiring the final 19 batters he faced. He struck out eight without a walk in the kind of clutch performance the Royals expected when they traded for him. connect with us The Globe and Mail Newspaper
